text: Lost Cabin is an unincorporated community in Fremont County, Wyoming. ==History== A post office called Lost Cabin was established in 1886, and remained in operation until 1966. The community received its name from a pioneer incident in which a party of prospectors escaped from Indians, only to find later their cabins had disappeared from the site. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Fremont County, Wyoming
title: Lost Cabin, Wyoming
